usage: nic_fw_updata.py [-h] [-n CYCLE_COUNT] [-i CHECK_IP] [-c CLEARLOG] -u
                        UPDATA_FILE -d DOWN_FILE

please input the parameter EX :
python3 nic_fw_updata.py 
-i 192.168.2.2 
-u /root/nicfw-up-down/fw-ConnectX5-rel-16_30_1004-MCX512A-ACA_Ax_Bx-
UEFI-14.23.17-FlexBoot-3.6.301.bin 
-d /root/nicfw-up-down/fw-
ConnectX5-rel-16_31_1014-MCX512A-ACA_Ax_Bx-UEFI-14.24.13-FlexBoot-3.6.403.bin
-n 4 
-c True

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -n CYCLE_COUNT, --cycle_count CYCLE_COUNT
                        please input NIC FW updata counts
  -i CHECK_IP, --check_ip CHECK_IP
                        please input checkip
  -c CLEARLOG, --clearlog CLEARLOG
                        please input -c True to clean log before test default
                        False
  -u UPDATA_FILE, --updata_file UPDATA_FILE
                        please input the NIC up FW file
  -d DOWN_FILE, --down_file DOWN_FILE
                        please input the down up FW file
